{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-bde79cbf202e7fc9", "type": "tool_result", "content": "=== 2602.15749 ===\n# A Generative-First Neural Audio Autoencoder\narXiv: 2602.15749\nAuthors: Jonah Casebeer, Ge Zhu, Zhepei Wang, Nicholas J. Bryan\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: codec_vae\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. A generative-first architecture for audio autoencoding that increases temporal downsampling from 2048× to 3360× and supports continuous and discrete representations alongside common audio channel formats in a single model.\n  2. Encoder architectural modifications including efficient activations, early downsampling, and strategic attention placement enable aggressive tokenization with substantial computational speedups.\n  3. Training improvements with audio channel format data augmentation and specialized loss functions enhance model generalization and robustness.\n  4. An optional post-training step discretizes a trained continuous model to support both continuous and discrete latents without retraining the backbone.\n\nTags: 压缩, 压缩/量化-RVQ, 压缩/量化-VAE\n\n=== 2604.22209 ===\n# UniSonate: A Unified Model for Speech, Music, and Sound Effect Generation with Text Instructions\narXiv: 2604.22209\nAuthors: \nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose UniSonate, the first flow-matching framework to unify TTS, TTM, and TTA tasks under a consistent, reference-free natural language instruction interface.\n  2. We introduce Dynamic Token Injection, a mechanism that symbolically represents unstructured acoustic events, enabling precise duration control for sound effects within a phoneme-driven architecture.\n  3. Extensive experiments demonstrate that UniSonate achieves state-of-the-art performance in instruction-based TTS and TTM while exhibiting positive transfer where joint training enhances structural coherence and prosodic expressiveness over single-task baselines.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-NAR-Flow, TTS/控制-NL描述, TTS/功能-多任务统一\n\n=== 2605.17085 ===\n# Taming Audio VAEs via Target-KL Regularization\narXiv: 2605.17085\nAuthors: Prem Seetharaman, Rithesh Kumar\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Target-KL regularization is introduced as a novel method to train continuous VAEs at specific target bitrates by directly regressing the KL divergence term.\n  2. A unified study of the rate-distortion trade-off is provided for both continuous and discrete audio compression models.\n  3. The impact of varying compression rates on downstream diffusion-based text-to-audio generative models is systematically evaluated.\n  4. The DAC architecture is adapted to a continuous VAE setting with improved training modifications that achieve state-of-the-art audio compression quality across bitrates.\n\nTags: 压缩, 压缩/量化-VAE\n\n=== 2508.11326 ===\n# MoE-TTS: Enhancing Out-of-Domain Text Understanding for Description-based TTS via Mixture-of-Experts\narXiv: 2508.11326\nAuthors: Heyang Xue, Xuchen Song, Yu Tang, Jianyu Chen, Yanru Chen, Yang Li, Yahui Zhou\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We are the first to focus on the performance of description-based TTS with out-of-domain descriptions to bridge the gap between research and real-world applications.\n  2. MoE-TTS is the first work to apply mixture-of-experts techniques to enhance TTS models by leveraging the pre-trained knowledge and text understanding capabilities of textual LLMs.\n  3. Our design surpasses state-of-the-art commercial models in generating speech that is more aligned with both in-domain and out-of-domain descriptions.\n\nTags: TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/控制-NL描述, TTS/控制-指令合成\n\n=== 2602.08794 ===\n# MOVA: Towards Scalable and Synchronized Video-Audio Generation\narXiv: 2602.08794\nAuthors: \nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We develop MOVA, a synchronized video-audio generation model with an asymmetric dual-tower architecture that leverages pre-trained video and audio generation models.\n  2. We design a fine-grained audio-video captioning pipeline to produce high-quality bimodal training data at scale.\n  3. By scaling video-audio training, we achieve continuous improvements in synchronization performance across both modalities.\n\nTags: related-work, we develop, we design, by scaling\n\n=== 2602.05207 ===\n# ARCHI-TTS: A flow-matching-based Text-to-Speech Model with Self-supervised Semantic Aligner and Accelerated Inference\narXiv: 2602.05207\nAuthors: Chunyat Wu, Jiajun Deng, Zhengxi Liu, Zheqi Dai, Haolin He, Qiuqiang Kong\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Introduction of a self-supervised semantic aligner that generates flexible-length, text-aligned semantic representations to ensure robust temporal and semantic consistency between text and audio.\n  2. Development of a training-free inference acceleration strategy that reuses condition encoder features across denoising steps to drastically reduce computational overhead.\n  3. Integration of an auxiliary CTC loss on the condition encoder to enhance the semantic understanding and alignment of the model.\n  4. Adoption of a compressed, low-token-rate VAE latent representation to reduce temporal redundancy and eliminate the need for a separate complex vocoder.\n  5. Incorporation of a velocity direction loss and logit-normal timestep sampling to accelerate convergence and improve synthesis quality.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-NAR-Flow, TTS/功能-DiT, TTS/功能-快速生成\n\n=== 2510.13344 ===\n# UniMoE-Audio: Unified Speech and Music Generation with Dynamic-Capacity MoE\narXiv: 2510.13344\nAuthors: Zhenyu Liu, Yunxin Li, Xuanyu Zhang, Qixun Teng, Shenyuan Jiang, Xinyu Chen, Haoyuan Shi, Jinchao Li, Qi Wang, Haolan Chen, Fanbo Meng, Mingjun Zhao, Yu Xu, Yancheng He, Baotian Hu, Min Zhang\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose UniMoE-Audio, a unified speech and music generation model based on a novel Dynamic-Capacity MoE framework that integrates a Top-P routing strategy and a hybrid expert design to mitigate inherent task conflict.\n  2. We introduce a data-aware, three-stage training curriculum that systematically overcomes data imbalance through independent specialist training, router warmup, and synergistic joint training.\n  3. We provide extensive experiments demonstrating that UniMoE-Audio achieves state-of-the-art or competitive performance on major speech and music generation benchmarks while revealing valuable insights into the dynamic activation patterns of the unified MoE model.\n\nTags: TTS\n\n=== 2602.17097 ===\n# AudioChat: Unified Audio Storytelling, Editing, and Understanding with Transfusion Forcing\narXiv: 2602.17097\nAuthors: William Chen, Prem Seetharaman, Rithesh Kumar, Oriol Nieto, Shinji Watanabe, Justin Salamon, Zeyu Jin\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: audio_understanding\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We develop AudioCopilot, a scalable pipeline for generating realistic audio scenes from scratch.\n  2. With the data generated from AudioCopilot, we develop AudioChat, the first unified model for generating, editing, and understanding audio stories with both speech and non-speech audio via structured reasoning.\n  3. We propose three novel evaluation metrics that overcome the weaknesses of standard audio generation metrics by directly measuring the task performance of audio generation and editing models.\n\nTags: LALM, LALM/对话型-交错标记, LALM/潜在表示", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "5f6b4c4f-7999-4c36-8879-0ad9909619fb", "uuid": "e41c77d4-95c7-424f-bb4b-b5d7ba10dfa2", "timestamp": "2026-07-12T19:18:41.815Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "=== 2602.15749 ===\n# A Generative-First Neural Audio Autoencoder\narXiv: 2602.15749\nAuthors: Jonah Casebeer, Ge Zhu, Zhepei Wang, Nicholas J. Bryan\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: codec_vae\nSta